## 1. ESXi Host Commands

| Command | Description | Usage |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| `vmware -v` | Check ESXi version | Show the installed ESXi version. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/getallvms` | List all VMs on the host | Display all virtual machines running on the ESXi host. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/power.on <VMID>` | Power on a VM | Power on a specific virtual machine. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/power.off <VMID>` | Power off a VM | Power off a specific virtual machine. |
| `services.sh restart` | Restart management agents | Restart the management agents on the ESXi host. |
| `esxcli network nic list` | List all network interfaces | Show all network interfaces on the host. |
| `esxcli network ip connection list` | View active network connections | Show all active network connections on the host. |
| `esxcli hardware platform get` | Check uptime | Display the uptime of the ESXi host. |
| `esxcli hardware get` | Get hardware information | Display detailed hardware information of the ESXi host. |
| `esxcli system health status get` | Check system health | Show the health status of the ESXi host. |
| `vim-cmd hostsvc/hostsummary` | View host configuration | Display the host configuration summary. |
| `esxcli hardware cpu list` | Show CPU information | Display CPU details. |
| `esxcli memory get` | Show memory usage | Display memory usage on the host. |
| `esxcli software vib list` | List installed patches | Show all installed patches and VIBs. |
| `vim-cmd hostsvc/configinfo` | Get host configuration | Display the current host configuration. |

---

## 2. VM and Resource Management

| Command | Description | Usage |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/migrate <VMID> <destination_host>` | Migrate a VM using vMotion | Move a virtual machine to another host using vMotion. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/snapshot.get <VMID>` | List VM snapshots | Display all snapshots for a specific VM. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/snapshot.create <VMID> <snapshot_name> <description>` | Create a snapshot | Create a new snapshot for a VM. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/snapshot.removeall <VMID>` | Remove all snapshots | Delete all snapshots for a virtual machine. |
| `esxtop` | Monitor ESXi performance | Monitor CPU and memory performance. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/get.resource <VMID>` | View VM resource allocation | Display resource allocations for a VM. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/nic.add <VMID> <adapter_type> <network_name>` | Add a VM network adapter | Add a network adapter to a virtual machine. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/reconfig <VMID> <new_config>` | Change VM resource allocation | Reconfigure the resource allocation for a VM. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/clone <VMID> <new_name>` | Clone a VM | Clone an existing virtual machine. |
| `vim-cmd vmsvc/create <VM_Name> <Datastore> <VM_ID>` | Create a new VM | Create a new virtual machine. |

---

## 3. ESXi Host Maintenance

| Command | Description | Usage |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| `vim-cmd hostsvc/maintenance_mode_enter` | Enable maintenance mode | Put the ESXi host into maintenance mode. |
| `vim-cmd hostsvc/maintenance_mode_exit` | Exit maintenance mode | Take the ESXi host out of maintenance mode. |
| `reboot` | Reboot ESXi host | Reboot the host. |
| `shutdown` | Shutdown ESXi host | Shutdown the host. |
| `vim-cmd hostsvc/services list` | List services | Show all services running on the host. |
| `esxcli system hostname set --host=<new_hostname>` | Change hostname | Set a new hostname for the ESXi host. |
| `esxcli system maintenanceMode set --enable` | Enable maintenance mode | Reset the ESXi host. |

---

## 4. Troubleshooting and Logs

| Command | Description | Usage |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| `cat /var/log/vmkernel.log` | View ESXi logs | Show ESXi system logs. |
| `tail -f /vmfs/volumes/<datastore>/<vm_name>/vmware.log` | Check VM logs | View log files for a specific virtual machine. |
| `esxcli system syslog config get` | View hardware logs | Show hardware-related logs. |
| `esxcli system syslog reload` | Clear ESXi logs | Reload the system logs after clearing. |
| `esxtop -b` | Check VM performance | View performance metrics for virtual machines. |
| `esxtop -m` | Monitor memory usage | Monitor the memory usage of virtual machines. |

---

## 5. Networking and Security

| Command | Description | Usage |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| `esxcli network firewall ruleset list` | List firewall rules | Display all active firewall rules. |
| `esxcli network firewall ruleset set --ruleset-id=<ruleset_name> --enabled=true` | Enable a firewall rule | Enable a specific firewall rule on the host. |
| `vmkping <ip_address>` | Test network connectivity | Ping a network IP address to check connectivity. |
| `esxcli network ip dns search list` | Display DNS configuration | Show the DNS search configuration for the host. |
| `esxcli network vswitch standard portgroup list` | List VLANs | Display all VLANs on the host. |
| `esxcli network vswitch standard list` | View vSwitch statistics | Display traffic statistics for a virtual switch. |

---

## 6. Storage Management

| Command | Description | Usage |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| `esxcli storage core device stats get --device=<device_name>` | Display storage statistics | Show performance stats for a storage device. |
| `esxcli storage vmfs extent list` | List VMFS datastores | Display all VMFS datastores. |
| `esxcli storage vmfs create --volume-label=<label> --device=<device_name>` | Create a VMFS datastore | Create a new VMFS datastore. |
| `esxcli storage vmfs unmount --volume-label=<label>` | Unmount a datastore | Unmount a VMFS datastore. |
| `esxcli storage core adapter rescan --adapter=<adapter_name>` | Rescan a storage adapter | Rescan a specific storage adapter for devices. |

---

## 7. Miscellaneous Commands

| Command | Description | Usage |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| `esxcli system settings advanced list` | Display ESXi configuration | Show advanced system settings. |
| `esxcli system service list` | List services | Show all running services on the ESXi host. |
| `esxcli software vib list` | Check installed VIBs | List all installed VMware Installation Bundles (VIBs). |
| `esxcli software vib update --depot=<depot_file>` | Update a VIB | Update a VIB using a depot file. |
| `esxcli system ntp start` | Start NTP service | Start the NTP service on the ESXi host. |
| `esxcli system ntp sync` | Sync time with NTP server | Sync the time on the ESXi host with an NTP server. |
| `vim-cmd vimsvc/license --show` | Display host license | Show the current ESXi host license information. |

---


